This paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms for testing the consistency of data sets with separable preferences. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which makes it relevant to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses economic implications of the results, which could place it in the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
